	(text_box "This boot & reset circuitry is recommended by ST, as documented in the Acheron Project Document Article (https://acheronproject.com/reset_article_1/reset_article_1/). "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 24.13 163.83 0)
		(size 58.42 11.43)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "423d85c7-9837-4f8e-9caa-6f2654b91f38")
	)
	(text_box "The STM32F072 was chosen for crystal-less USB support using its Clock-Recovery System, QMK support, USB-DFU bootloader, support for extra features -- like I2C, PWM, SPI -- and because it is widely used in the keyboard designing community."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 91.44 163.83 0)
		(size 81.28 13.97)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "b2adc83a-bc9d-4761-8e25-448fd6f17bd8")
	)
	(text_box "The pins for SWD are broken out to allow debugging and low-level programming of the STM32F072. Firmware flashing during normal use will be performed via USB using the built-in DFU bootloader."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 227.33 97.79 0)
		(size 34.29 16.2161)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(color 72 72 72 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "c42f536b-a218-4c28-9b5b-8194a7875e49")
	)
	(text_box "The decoupling capacitors for the STM32 VDD pins. There is one 0.1 uF capacitor per pin and a 10 uF bulk capacitor."
